id: pm-ikv6m0
title: "Recovery bundle mines flag names from usage-error prose: scope errors like '--rebuild and --clear apply only to graph index' yield missing:--clear + suggested_retry appending the other invalid flag"
description: "Observed with pm graph analyze --rebuild (2026-07-20 manual E2E): the usage error '--rebuild and --clear apply only to graph index.' produces recovery.missing: --clear and suggested_retry: 'pm graph analyze --rebuild --clear' — the exact opposite of the fix. The recovery generator extracts flag tokens from arbitrary error MESSAGE prose and treats them as missing required flags. Sibling of the arity lineage (pm-6y58/pm-9qcr fixed arity, not provenance): flags named in a scope/mutual-exclusion explanation are not missing inputs. Fix direction: only derive missing-flag suggestions from structured metadata (contract-declared required flags), never from message text; scope/exclusivity usage errors should suggest removing the offending flag or switching subcommand."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,cli,error-recovery
created_at: "2026-07-20T03:19:23.954Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-20T03:45:22.539Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: Scope/mutual-exclusion usage errors produce no missing-flag rows and no suggested_retry that adds another invalid flag; missing-flag derivation consults only structured contract metadata; regression covers the graph --rebuild/--clear and --save-baseline scope errors
